# CoalMine — 9 Quality Canaries

Skills live in `.cursor/skills/` (one `SKILL.md` each). Invoke by keyword; each skill gates its own tier and fix menus — never fix without the menu.

| Trigger | Use when |
|---|---|
| `/rotcanary` · "code-health" | scan for code rot — dead code, leaks, silent failures, doc rot |
| `/gold-standard` · "audit rules" | score completeness vs world-class exemplars; fill/adopt/conform |
| `/source-grounding` | verify version-sensitive facts against live sources |
| `/supply-chain-audit` | deps/CVEs/licenses/build trust — before adding a dep or a release |
| `/resilience-audit` | failure modes (FMEA) — network, storage, async, retry/rollback paths |
| `/telemetry-canary` | logging, metrics, tracing, error-handling changes |
| `/testability-canary` | coupling, DI, mockability refactors |
| `/scale-canary` | loops over growing data, DB queries, caches, event-loop code |
| `/drift-canary` | DB schema, API contract, serialized payload, required config changes |

**Proactive:** when the conversation moves into one of these areas, OFFER the matching canary via your question tool (Run now / Queue / Skip) — do not run unasked: deps → supply-chain · schema/API → drift · async/retry → resilience · hot loops/queries → scale · tests/coupling → testability · logging/metrics → telemetry.

**Session end:** if code files were modified, run `/rotcanary` on them (QUICK, report only) and surface CRITICAL/HIGH findings before finishing. Do not block work.
